<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[94,623,288,1425]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">
IDENTIFICATION: Previously regarded as monotypic (e.g., by 
<bibRefCitation author="Koopman, K. F." box="[329,521,376,399]" editor="D. E. Wilson &amp; D. M. Reeder" journalOrPublisher="Washington, DC: Smithson. Inst. Press" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" refId="ref96667" refString="1993. Order Chiroptera. In D. E. Wilson and D. M. Reeder (eds.), Mammal species of the World, a taxonomic and geographic reference, 2 nd ed.: 137 - 241. Washington, DC: Smithson. Inst. Press." title="Order Chiroptera" type="book" volumeTitle="Mammal species of the World, a taxonomic and geographic reference, 2 nd" year="1993">Koopman, 1993</bibRefCitation>
), the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[150,323,405,428]" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Centronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[150,323,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Centronycteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently shown to contain at least two species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons, N. B. &amp; C. O. Handley, Jr." bookContentInfo="28 pp." journalOrPublisher="Am. Mus. Novitates 3239" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" refId="ref100379" refString="Simmons, N. B., and C. O. Handley, Jr. 1998. A revision of Centronycteris Gray (Chiroptera: Emballonuridae) with notes on natural history. Am. Mus. Novitates 3239: 28 pp." title="A revision of Centronycteris Gray (Chiroptera: Emballonuridae) with notes on natural history" type="book" year="1998">Simmons and Handley (1998)</bibRefCitation>
. According to these authors, the known range of 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Centronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximiliani">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Centronycteris maximiliani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes southern Venezuela, the Guianas, and northern, eastern, and southeastern Brazil, whereas 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomas (1912 b)" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1912" box="[284,622,581,604]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Promops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centralis">
<emphasis box="[284,303,581,604]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[319,421,581,604]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">centralis</emphasis>
Thomas (1912b)
</taxonomicName>
occurs in Central America, Colombia, Peru, and on both sides of the Andes in Ecuador. Both species are known from only a few specimens, however, and their true geographic ranges may be considerably larger. In fact, because no known biogeographic barriers separate the ranges of 
<taxonomicName box="[361,536,786,810]" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Centronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximiliani">
<emphasis box="[361,380,787,810]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[397,536,787,810]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">maximiliani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1912" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Promops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centralis">
<emphasis box="[595,614,787,810]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[94,196,816,839]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">centralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, these bats might occur sympatrically almost anywhere in Amazonia. Our Paracou voucher is the first known specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[128,304,904,927]" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Centronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximiliani">
<emphasis box="[128,147,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[165,304,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">maximiliani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from French Guiana.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[94,623,288,1425]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">
Measurements and descriptions of 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Centronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximiliani">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Centronycteris maximiliani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Guianas and elsewhere were provided by Thomas (1913), 
<bibRefCitation author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." box="[94,260,1021,1044]" journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978), 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, S. L. &amp; H. H. Genoways &amp; J. A. Groen" box="[357,617,1021,1044]" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Carnegie Mus." pageId="24" pageNumber="24" pagination="329 - 336" part="52" refId="ref102492" refString="Williams, S. L., H. H. Genoways, and J. A. Groen 1983. Results of the Alcoa Foundation-Suriname Expeditions. VII. Records of mammals from central and southern Suriname. Ann. Carnegie Mus. 52: 329 - 336." title="Results of the Alcoa Foundation-Suriname Expeditions. VII. Records of mammals from central and southern Suriname" type="journal article" year="1983">Williams et al. (1983)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons, N. B. &amp; C. O. Handley, Jr." bookContentInfo="28 pp." box="[144,499,1050,1073]" journalOrPublisher="Am. Mus. Novitates 3239" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" refId="ref100379" refString="Simmons, N. B., and C. O. Handley, Jr. 1998. A revision of Centronycteris Gray (Chiroptera: Emballonuridae) with notes on natural history. Am. Mus. Novitates 3239: 28 pp." title="A revision of Centronycteris Gray (Chiroptera: Emballonuridae) with notes on natural history" type="book" year="1998">Simmons and Handley (1998)</bibRefCitation>
. The latter authors summarized craniodental characters and measurements that distinguish 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Centronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximiliani">
<emphasis box="[518,537,1109,1132]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">maximiliani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1912" box="[277,432,1138,1162]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Promops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centralis">
<emphasis box="[277,296,1139,1162]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[322,432,1139,1162]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">centralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our Paracou voucher formed much of the basis of their description of 
<taxonomicName box="[267,442,1197,1220]" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Centronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximiliani">
<emphasis box="[267,286,1197,1220]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[303,442,1197,1220]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">maximiliani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
